# Alouma Web design direction

Alouma should feel calm, premium, editorial, and practical.

## Visual tone

Use:
- restrained surfaces
- strong typography
- clear hierarchy
- generous but controlled spacing
- neutral base palette
- mustard accent carefully
- subtle motion only when useful

Avoid:
- generic SaaS gradients
- heavy glassmorphism
- noisy cards everywhere
- childish mascot overuse
- fake trust badges
- aggressive sales language

## Brand palette direction

Core direction:
- Jet / near-black
- Silver / cool neutral
- Mustard accent

Use a 60/30/10 mindset:
- 60% neutral surfaces/background
- 30% text/structure/depth
- 10% accent

## UX principles

- Make the next step obvious.
- Keep copy human and recruiter-grounded.
- Do not overexplain.
- Avoid AI-fluff.
- Preserve a calm guided flow.
- Empty states should be useful, not decorative.

## Layout

Desktop web can adapt from iOS but should not feel like a stretched phone screen.

Good web patterns:
- sidebar or split-pane for app shell
- larger preview canvas
- editor + preview side-by-side later
- clean route-level pages
- readable forms

## CV preview

The CV itself is not a decorative component.

Do not apply app-card styling inside the CV document.
The CV document must remain print-stable and recruiter-readable.
